netcat : netcat is a computer networking utility for reading from and writing to network connections using TCP or UDP. The command is designed to be a dependable back-end that can be used directly or easily driven by other programs and scripts.

to open connextion using netcat : 
`nc YOUR_ULR YOUR_PORT`

So, to open the connexion for the website given we do :
`nc jupiter.challenges.picoctf.org 25103`

it will give us diractly the flag : picoCTF{nEtCat_Mast3ry_d0c64587}

More Information :
https://linux.die.net/man/1/nc